.TH "evergreen_copy_dma" 9 "evergreen_copy_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
evergreen_copy_dma \- copy pages using the DMA engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct radeon_fence *" evergreen_copy_dma
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "uint64_t src_offset "  ","
.BI "uint64_t dst_offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned num_gpu_pages "  ","
.BI "struct dma_resv *resv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon_device pointer
.IP "src_offset" 12
src GPU address
.IP "dst_offset" 12
dst GPU address
.IP "num_gpu_pages" 12
number of GPU pages to xfer
.IP "resv" 12
reservation object with embedded fence
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Copy GPU paging using the DMA engine (evergreen-cayman).
Used by the radeon ttm implementation to move pages if
registered as the asic copy callback.
